==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fr|en}} {{term|acidité|lang=fr}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|aciditātem|lang=la}}, accusative singular of {{term/t|la|aciditās||sourness, acidity}}, from {{term|acidus||sour, acid|lang=la}}. See [[acid]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/əˈsɪdɪti/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|acidities}}

# The [[quality]] or state of being acid
# The quality of [[sour]]; [[sourness]]; [[tartness]]; [[sharpness]] to the taste, as in the '''acidity''' of lemon juice.
#: ''Empty stomachs lead to '''acidity''' and leave a sour taste in the mouth.''
# {{context|pathology|lang=en}} Excessive acid quality, as in [[gastric]] [[secretions]].

